The following examples demonstrate how to retrieve a breakdown of the
score using the [$search](pipe.$search) `scoreDetails` option for the
documents in the results for the [text](text-ref), [near](near-ref),
[compound](compound-ref), and [embeddedDocument](embedded-document-ref) operator queries.**Text:**textThe following example uses the [text](text-ref) operator to query
the `title` field in the `sample_mflix.movies` collection for
the term `autumn`. The query  specifies the `scoreDetails`
option in the [$search](pipe.$search) stage to retrieve a detailed
breakdown of the score for each document in the results. The query
uses the [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) stage to limit the results to three
documents and the [$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to do the following:* Exclude the `_id` field.

* Include only the `title` field.

* Add the `score` field to the results to return the score of the
  document and the `scoreDetails` field to the results to return a
  detailed breakdown of the score for the document.**Input:**```json
db.movies.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "text": {
        "path": "title",
        "query": "autumn"
      },
      "scoreDetails": true
    }
  },
  {
    "$limit": 3
  },
  {
    "$project": {
      "_id": 0,
      "title": 1,
      "score": { "$meta": "searchScore" },
      "scoreDetails": { "$meta": "searchScoreDetails" }
    }
  }
])
```**Output:**```json
