> represent the [compound](compound-ref) operator query `filter` clause,
> which doesn't contribute to the score of the document.**Embedded:**embeddedDocumentThe following example uses the [embeddedDocument](embedded-document-ref)
operator to query the `products.name` field in the
`sample_training.companies` collection for products that contain
the term `Basic` preceded by any number of other characters. The
query specifies inside the `embeddedDocument` operator that the
returned score must be a sum of all the matching embedded
documents. The query also specifies the `scoreDetails` option in
the [$search](pipe.$search) stage to retrieve a detailed breakdown of
the score for each document in the results. The query uses the
[$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) stage to limit the results to three documents
and the [$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to do the following:* Exclude the `_id` field.

* Include only the `products.name` field.

* Add the `score` field to the results to return the score of the
  document and the `scoreDetails` field to the results to return a
  detailed breakdown of the score for the document.**Input:**```json
db.companies.aggregate({
  "$search": {
    "embeddedDocument": {
      "path": "products",
      "operator": {
        "wildcard": {
          "path": "products.name",
          "query": "*Basic",
          "allowAnalyzedField": true
        }
     },
      "score": {
        "embedded": {
          "aggregate": "sum"
        }
      }
    },
    "scoreDetails": true
  }
},
{
  "$limit": 3
},
{
  "$project": {
    "_id": 0,
    "name": 1,
    "products.name": 1,
    "score": { "$meta": "searchScore" },
    "scoreDetails": { "$meta": "searchScoreDetails" }
  }
})
